Police in Turkana County on Wednesday arrested a 45-year-old man in possession of a firearm, ammunition and an assortment of other goods meant for security agents. Peter Lolimo was arrested in his rented house in Kanamkemer village by officers from Lodwar Police Station who were acting on a tip-off from area residents. In a statement issued on Wednesday, the National Police Service (NPS) said police officers on patrol raided the rented premises the suspect was occupying and recovered the illegally owned items. "A search in the house revealed a Luger Pistol with a fully loaded magazine, pistol holster, American jungle uniform, several pairs of uniforms belonging to different disciplined services in the country and a pair of handcuffs," read the statement. Lolimo was then escorted to Lodwar Police Station where he was detained awaiting arraignment. Further investigations are underway.  